## Installation

### From PyPI *(coming soon)*

```bash
pip install swissrenov
```

### From GitHub (latest development version)

```bash
pip install git+https://github.com/[YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME]/swissrenov.git
```

### For contributors / local development

```bash
git clone https://github.com/[YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME]/swissrenov.git
cd swissrenov
pip install -e .
```

## Requirements

- Python >= 3.9
- numpy
- laspy
- open3d
- opencv-python
- matplotlib
- Pillow
- scipy

All dependencies are installed automatically via `pip`.

